headline.print_headline: Chile President Evacuated From Arica Coastline After Quake
headline.main: Chile President Evacuated From Arica Coastline After Quake

lead_paragraph: Chile's President Michelle Bachelet was evacuated from her hotel in the northern city of Arica after a strong 7.8 magnitude quake triggered a tsunami alert, local media reported on Thursday.
